[simple system admin coomands ]
1.BASIC LINUX COMMANDS
[------------------------------basic systemlookup-------------------------------]
			a.uptime or uptime -p to show in minutes.
			b.uname -a =print system information,kernel version,kernel release,hostname.
			c.to view the size of file system df-h
			d.du -h absuolute/filename = will show disk space use or to see total usasge us du -hs filename.
			e.free -h to see total use and free system memory.
			f.ps aux to see current process running.
			g.top to see greedy process
			h.to view domain information dig sitename ANY.
			i.to view user logged on who or w(for more verbose).
			j.to find the file in directory use find
			k.to see mermory info cat /proc/meminfo.
			l.to remove file completly by overwriting 7 time and add final zero to hide shredding shred -fzv -n 10 filename.
			m.to view cpu details lscpu.
			n.system overview command inxi -Fxz
			o.to list each memorystick and its capacity sudo dmidecode -t memory 
			p.w to view all the user shells and more info.



[--------------------------------compression----------------------------------]
			a.to create an archive tar -cvf filename.tar orginalfile
			b.to create an archive with gzip tar -cvzf tarfilename.gz fileordir
			c.to create an archive with bz2 compression tar -cvjf filename.tar.bz2 file or dir.
			d.to create an archive with xz compression tar -cvJf filenamr.tar.xz file
			e.to extract a tar archive use tar -xvf tar_filename.
			f.to create a 7z archive file tar a filename.
			g.to extract 7z archive file tar e filename.7z.
			h.7z a -tzip[or any like gzip xz ]
			i.to test intergrity of 7z 7z t filename 
			j.to set password to an archive file 7za a -p pasword here filename.
			k.untar singlefile tar -xvf cleanfiles.sh.tar filename.for zip use -xvxf or use -jxvf.
			l.to add files or directory to tar file use tar -rvf filenamr.tar xyz.txt(it will be added).
			m.to view tar archive file without listing tar -tvf filename.tar or 7z l filename or zip -sf  filename.zip 
			n.to view the content of rarfile rar l filename.rar 
			o.to open rar file unrar e filename.rar
			p.to rar the file use rar a filename.rar realfile
			q.to set password to rar file rar a -p filename.rar and to lock from extractin it rar k filename.rar.





[--------------------------------networking----------------------------------]				
iproute show to print or display the routing table.
traceroute hostname to view all the route taken by packets.
to view all listening ports netstat -ltu
to view statistcs of all port netstat -s
to ping the host ping hostname.

	
